## Description

We can create and manage buckets with `ovh_cloud_project_storage`, but it is not possible at this time to set a [bucket's ACL](https://docs.ovhcloud.com/en/guides/storage-and-backup/object-storage/s3-bucket-acl) (e.g. `public-read`) with the OVH Terraform provider.

This is needed to expose a bucket publicly, and is a prerequisite for [S3 website hosting](https://docs.ovhcloud.com/en/guides/storage-and-backup/object-storage/s3-website). At this time, we have to mix in the AWS provider and use its [aws_s3_bucket_acl](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs/resources/s3_bucket_acl) resource (pointed at the OVHcloud S3 endpoint) to configure it. Having it natively in the OVH provider would avoid pulling in a second provider just for this.

### Requested Resource(s) and/or Data Source(s)

* `ovh_cloud_project_storage_acl`

### Potential Terraform Configuration

```hcl
resource "ovh_cloud_project_storage" "assets" {
  service_name = "<public cloud project ID>"
  region_name  = "EU-WEST-PAR"
  name         = "assets"
}

resource "ovh_cloud_project_storage_acl" "assets" {
  service_name = "<public cloud project ID>"
  region_name  = "EU-WEST-PAR"
  bucket       = ovh_cloud_project_storage.assets.name
  acl          = "public-read"
}

resource "ovh_cloud_project_storage_website" "assets" {
  service_name = "<public cloud project ID>"
  region_name  = "EU-WEST-PAR"
  bucket       = ovh_cloud_project_storage.assets.name

  index_document {
    suffix = "index.html"
  }

  error_document {
    key = "error.html"
  }
}
```

Also see [`ovh_cloud_project_storage_website`](https://github.com/ovh/terraform-provider-ovh/issues/1340)

### Description

We can create and manage buckets with `ovh_cloud_project_storage`, but it is not possible at this time to set up static website hosting with [S3 Website](https://docs.ovhcloud.com/en/guides/storage-and-backup/object-storage/s3-website) (index document, error document, redirects) on them with the OVH Terraform provider.

At this time, we have to use the AWS provider and the [`aws_s3_bucket_website_configuration` resource](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs/resources/s3_bucket_website_configuration) to configure the website. Having it natively in the OVH provider would avoid pulling in a second provider just for this.

### Requested Resource(s) and/or Data Source(s)

* `ovh_cloud_project_storage_website`

### Potential Terraform Configuration

```hcl
resource "ovh_cloud_project_storage" "assets" {
  service_name = "<public cloud project ID>"
  region_name  = "EU-WEST-PAR"
  name         = "assets"
}

resource "ovh_cloud_project_storage_website" "assets" {
  service_name = "<public cloud project ID>"
  region_name  = "EU-WEST-PAR"
  bucket       = ovh_cloud_project_storage.assets.name

  index_document {
    suffix = "index.html"
  }

  error_document {
    key = "error.html"
  }
}
```

Also see [`ovh_cloud_project_storage_acl`](https://github.com/ovh/terraform-provider-ovh/issues/1341)
